Steps to Reproduce:

1. Open a CSS file
2. Insert a line like: 	"background-color: #db030399;" in a CSS style
Example:
div.errorF {
	background-color: #db030399;
	border: 2px solid red;
	border-radius: 0.5em;
	margin: 0.5em;
	padding-left: 1em;
	padding-right: 1em;
	display: inline-block;
}

Reproduces without extensions: Yes

VS Code says that this line excepts a value and invalids the rest of the block, and its a valid color with alpha

